{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The embedding vector produced for a given query string has the correct dimensionality for the vector database index.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Failure boundary is at the real embedding-model output contract (model-selected dimension) handed to the vector index schema. A stubbed embedding can be forced to the expected size and would miss wrong-model/config regressions. Rejection gate: System was considered, but the behavior text is about embedding output validity, not OS/subprocess/network mechanics; the model output itself is the critical dependency.","test_description":"Call the real embedding model with representative queries and assert returned vector length exactly matches the live index dimension before insert/search.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.01,"Integration":0.2,"System":0.06,"Agentic":0.72,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"The similarity search returns results ordered by descending cosine similarity score.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is a cross-module invariant (search service + vector store adapter + score mapping/order), but it does not require real OS/network/subprocess or model-quality judgment. In-process wiring with controlled vectors can expose real ordering/score-handling bugs. Rejection gate: System rejected because behavior text does not require real network/OS effects; Agentic rejected because correctness does not depend on AI/ML judgment quality.","test_description":"Seed a test vector store with known vectors, execute similarity search through the service layer, and assert returned scores are monotonic descending with IDs in expected order.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.22,"Integration":0.63,"System":0.13,"Agentic":0.01,"Workflow":0.01}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The LLM re-ranking step changes the order of at least some resul